As a Robotics Engineer, you will play a vital role in our Research and Development department, performing a range of duties including designing and developing robotics systems products.

Trainee to be involved in:
1. Design and develop Drone and Ground based Robotics Systems.
2. Respond to all Robotics System-related issues and provide technical support to all staff members.
3. Conduct validation testing for device and algorithms.
4. Ensure existing research, development and testing equipment are up-to-date.
5. Stay up-to-date with the latest technologies and incorporate new technology into existing units.
6. Draft new project proposals and present them to management.
7. Plan and manage the product production tea

Technical skills Trainee will learn:

1. Develop functional and reliable robotics systems
2. Collaborate in an engineering team

Highest Qualification:
University Degree or above


Eligibility Criteria for SGUnitedTraineeships:•Singapore Citizen or Permanent Resident; anda.Graduated or graduating in calendar year 2019 or 2020 from ITEs, polytechnics, universities, or other educational institutions (e.g. private universities and overseas institutions); orb.Graduated earlier from above institutions and completed National Service in 2019 or 2020